  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid for Displaced Persons and Other Vulnerable People in Bangladesh and Myanmar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at improving human security through enhancing access to life-saving protection and multi sectoral humanitarian services in Bangladesh, by strengthening community-based protection through engagement, awareness raising, and sensitization; case management and specialized protection services for individuals in need to improve human security and peaceful coexistence between communities; provision of disaster risk reduction measures, site improvements and site planning interventions that enable equitable access to assistance, protection, and services for refugees living in the sites; strengthening and sustaining critical life-saving health services to the Rohingya population and host community in Cox&#x2019;s Bazar; and Implementing the second phase of the Transitional Shelter Assistance programme, to increase shelter strength, durability and habitability of existing shelters provided by IOM.</narrative>
  </description>
